      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"><a name="part1">PART
I</a></font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"><a name="item1">IT</a></font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"><a name="item1">EM&#160;1.
</a>BUSINESS</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">General</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Overview</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Republic Airways Holdings Inc. is a
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Delaware </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">holding company organized in 1996 that
owns three regional airlines: Chautauqua Airlines, Inc., (&#8220;Chautauqua
Airlines&#8221;), our operator of 37 to 50 seat aircraft; Shuttle America Corporation
(&#8220;Shuttle </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">America</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8221;), our operator of 70-seat aircraft;
and Republic Airline Inc. (&#8220;Republic Airline&#8221;), our operator of aircraft with
more than 70 seats.&#160;&#160;As of December 31, 2007, </font>our subsidiaries
offered scheduled passenger service on approximately 1,250 flights daily to 119
cities in 39 states, Canada, Mexico, Jamaica and the Bahamas pursuant to
code-share agreements with AMR Corp., the parent of American Airlines, Inc.
(&#8220;American&#8221;), Continental Airlines, Inc. (&#8220;Continental&#8221;), Delta Air Lines, Inc.
(&#8220;Delta&#8221;), Frontier Airlines, Inc. (&#8220;Frontier&#8221;), US Airways, Inc. (&#8220;US Airways&#8221;)
and United Air Lines, Inc. (&#8220;United&#8221;), collectively referred to as our
(&#8220;Partners&#8221;). We began flying for Continental and Frontier in January and March
2007, respectively. Currently, we provide our Partners with regional jet
service, operating as AmericanConnection, Continental Express, Delta Connection,
Frontier Airlines, US Airways Express, or United Express, including service out
of their hubs and focus cities in Atlanta, Boston, Denver, Chicago, Cincinnati,
Cleveland, Columbus, Houston, Indianapolis, New York, Philadelphia, Pittsburgh,
St. Louis and Washington, D.C. (Dulles and National).</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Unless
the context indicates otherwise, the terms &#8220;the Company,&#8221; &#8220;we,&#8221; &#8220;us,&#8221; or &#8220;our,&#8221;
refer to Republic Airways Holdings Inc. and its subsidiaries.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">We have long-term, fixed-fee regional
jet code-share agreements with each of our Partners that are subject to our
maintaining specified performance levels. Pursuant to these fixed-fee
agreements, which provide for minimum aircraft utilization at fixed rates, we
are authorized to use our Partners' two-character flight designation codes to
identify our flights and fares in our Partners' computer reservation systems, to
paint our aircraft in the style of our Partners, to use their service marks and
to market ourselves as a carrier for our Partners. In addition, in connection
with a marketing agreement among Delta, Continental and Northwest Airlines,
certain of the routes that we fly using Delta's and Continental&#8217;s flight
designator codes are also flown under Northwest's designator code. Our fixed-fee
agreements eliminate our exposure to fluctuations in fuel prices, fare
competition and passenger volumes. Our development of relationships with
multiple major airlines has enabled us to reduce our dependence on any single
airline, allocate our overhead more efficiently among our Partners and reduce
the cost of our services to our Partners.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">During 2007 we increased our</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> operational fleet </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">by 48 aircraft for a total
operation</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">al </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">fleet as of December 31, 2007 of
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">219 aircraft</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.&#160;&#160;Our operational fleet is
comprised of 101</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">
ERJ-170/175, 70-86 seat aircraft, 94 ERJ-145 family, 37-50 seat aircraft, and 24
CRJ-200, 50 seat aircraft. </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">During 2007 we added 44 </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">aircraft into service for Continental
by</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">transition</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">ing</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">20 ERJ</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">-145 aircraft from our US Airways
operation and </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">leasing
24</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">CRJ-200 aircraft</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.&#160;&#160;We added five ERJ-170
aircraft to Frontier by transitioning five ERJ-170 aircraft from our US Airways
operation.&#160;&#160;We also added 25 ERJ-175 aircraft for US Airways and
removed the five ERJ-170 aircraft and 20 ERJ-145 aircraft from the US Airways
operation.&#160;&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">In
addition, we removed</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> one
ERJ-145 aircraft from our charter service and subleased the aircraft to an
airline in </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Mexico</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Currently, we have agreed to place into
service an additional 29 ERJ-175 aircraft for our Partners through March 2009.
These 29 aircraft are covered by firm orders that we have with an
aircraft</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">
manufacturer.&#160;&#160;We expect to place 16 of these 29 aircraft into service
with Delta during the second half of 2008 and the first quarter of 2009, which
will replace the 16 ERJ-170 aircraft currently in operation with
Delta.&#160;&#160;Ten of the ERJ-170 aircraft removed from Delta will transition
to our United operation during the fourth quarter of 2008 and the first quarter
of 2009; five of the ERJ-170 aircraft removed from Delta will transition to our
Frontier operation during 2008; and one of the aircraft removed from Delta is
currently unallocated to our Partners.&#160;&#160;We expect to place the
remaining 13 of the 29 ERJ-175 aircraft into service with US Airways during
2008.&#160;&#160;Three of these aircraft will replace three ERJ-170 aircraft
that will transition to Frontier during 2008.&#160;&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The Company has options for 74 ERJ-170
aircraft, which may be converted to options for ERJ-175, ERJ-190 or ERJ-195
aircraft, which range in size from 78 seats to 110
seats.&#160;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Under our amended Delta agreement, we
agreed to remove from service all 15 of our ERJ-135 at a rate of two aircraft
per month beginning in September 2008.&#160;&#160;We expect to sell these
aircraft to Embraer or another party as the aircraft are removed from
service.&#160;&#160;Under our Continental agreement, we expect all 24 CRJ-200
aircraft to be removed from service and returned to the
lessor.&#160;&#160;Currently, we anticipate removing seven aircraft in the
fourth quarter of 2008, 10 aircraft in 2009 and seven aircraft in
2010.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">For the years ended December 31,
2007</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, 2006 and 2005
respectively, Delta accounted for approximately 33%, 35% and 34%, United
accounted for approximately 24%, 30% and 32%, US Airways accounted for
approximately 22%, 24% and 21% and American accounted for approximately 9%, 11%
and 13% of our regional airline services revenues. Continental and Frontier
accounted for approximately 10% and 2%, respectively, of our regional airline
services revenues for the year ended December 31, 2007.</font></font></div><br>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"><a name="routes">Markets and
Routes</a></font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Markets</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">We believe that the development of hub
operations in St. Louis with American; in New York, Boston, Indianapolis,
Philadelphia, Pittsburgh and Washington, D.C. with US Airways; in Columbus,
Atlanta and Cincinnati with Delta; in Chicago and Washington</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> D.C. with United, in Houston and
Cleveland with Continental and in Denver with Frontier has been a principal
factor in the growth of our flight operations and will facilitate implementation
of our growth and operating strategy. As of December 31, 2007, we offered
scheduled passenger service on approximately </font>1,250 flights daily to 119
cities in 39 states, Canada, Mexico, Jamaica and the Bahamas<font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">. The following illustrates the routes
we currently fly for our Partners:</font></font></div><br>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">

      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">

      </div><br>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Maintenance of Aircraft and
Training</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Using a combination of Federal Aviation
Administration (&#8220;FAA</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8221;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">) certified maintenance vendors and our
own personnel and facilities, we maintain our aircraft on a scheduled and
"as-needed" basis. We emphasize preventive maintenance and inspect our aircraft
engines and airframes as required. During 2007, we entered into long-term
maintenance agreements for engines</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">,</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">auxiliary power units (&#8220;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">AP</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">U</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8221;) and other airframe components
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">for our CRJ-200
aircraft</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, which will cover
the aircraft during the short-term lease period of two to three
years</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">. Also, during 2007,
we entered into an agreement to maintain wheels and brakes on our ERJ-170/175
aircraft through February</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">
2017</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.&#160;&#160;We have an
agreement to maintain the engines on our ERJ-145 family of aircraft through
October 2012, an agreement to maintain the </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">AP</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Us on our ERJ-145 family of aircraft
through </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">June
2013</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, agreements to
maintain the avionics on our ERJ-145 family of aircraft and ERJ-170 family of
aircraft through December 2014, an agreement to maintain wheels and brakes on
our ERJ-145 family of aircraft through June 2014 and&#160;an agreement to
maintain the engines on our ERJ-170 family of aircraft through December
2014</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">. </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Under these agreements, we are charged
for covered services based on a fixed rate for each flight hour or flight cycle
accumulated by the engines or airframes in our service during each month. The
rates are subject to annual revisions, generally based on certain Bureau of
Labor Statistics' labor and material indices.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">We believe these agreements, coupled
with our ongoing maintenance program, reduce the likelihood of unexpected levels
of engine, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">AP</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">U, avionics and wheels and brakes
maintenance expense during their term.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">We perform our heavy and routine
maintenance projects at our facilities in </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Indianapolis</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Columbus</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Louisville</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Pittsburgh and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">St. Louis</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, and we perform routine maintenance
services from select line maintenance stations.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">All mechanics and avionics specialists
employed by us have appropriate training and experience and hold required
licenses issued by the FAA. We provide periodic in-house and outside training
for our maintenance and flight personnel and also take advantage of
manufacturers&#8217; training programs that are offered when acquiring new
aircraft.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">We have an agreement with Flight Safety
International to provide for aircraft simulator training for our pilots. We have
no current plans to acquire our own simulator in the near term and believe that
Flight Safety or other third party vendors will be able to provide us with
adequate and cost effective flight simulator training to implement our growth
plans.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Employees</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">As of December 31, 2007, we employed

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">As of December 31, 2007, we had
approximately 820 maintenance</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> technicians and other maintenance
related personnel, who are not currently represented by any union, and
approximately </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">260
administration</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> and support
personnel. Because of the high level of unionization among our employees we are
subject to risks of work interruption or stoppage and/or the incurrence of
additional expenses associated with union representation of our employees. We
have never experienced any work stoppages or other job actions and generally
consider our relationship with our employees to be good.</font></font></div>

                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Director</font></font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td align="left" valign="top" width="25%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Mark L. Plaumann&#160;
      &#160;&#160;</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td align="left" valign="top" width="9%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">52</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td align="left" valign="top" width="52%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Director</font></font></div>

      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Bryan&#160;K. Bedford joined us in
July&#160;1999 as our president and chief executive officer and a member of our
board of directors and became chairman of the board in August&#160;2001. From
July&#160;1995 through July&#160;1999, Mr.&#160;Bedford was the president and
chief executive officer and a director of Mesaba Holdings,&#160;Inc., a
publicly-owned regional airline. He has over 1</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">9</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;years of experience in the
regional airline industry, and was named regional airline executive of the year
in 1998 by Commuter and Regional Airline News and again in 2005 by Regional
Airline World magazine. Mr.&#160;Bedford is a licensed pilot and a certified
public accountant. He also served as the 1998 Chairman of the Regional Airline
Association (RAA), and remains on the Board of Directors of the
RAA.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Robert&#160;H. Cooper joined us in
August&#160;1999 as vice president and chief financial officer. In
February&#160;2002, he became executive vice president, chief financial officer,
treasurer and secretary and assumed responsibility for all purchasing and
material control. He was previously employed with Mesaba Holdings,&#160;Inc.
from September&#160;1995 through August&#160;1999 as its vice president, chief
financial officer and treasurer. Mr.&#160;Cooper is a certified public
accountant. He has over 1</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">4
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">years experience in the
regional airline industry. He has responsibility for financial accounting,
treasury, public reporting, investor relations, human resources, information
technology, purchasing and material control.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Wayne&#160;C. Heller joined us in
August&#160;1999 as Vice President&#8212;Flight Operations with responsibility for
flight crew supervision, system control, flight safety and flight quality
standards. In February&#160;2002, he became Executive Vice President and Chief
Operating Officer of Chautauqua, and assumed responsibility for all aircraft
maintenance, records and engineering. From April&#160;1996 until
August&#160;1999 he was employed by Mesaba Airlines,&#160;Inc., as its Director
of System Operations Control. He is a licensed pilot and a licensed dispatcher
and has over 2</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">6</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;years of regional airline
experience in operations.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Lawrence J. Cohen has been a director
since June 2002. He is the owner and Chairman of Pembroke Companies, Inc., an
investment and management firm that he founded in 1991. The firm makes
investments in and provides strategic management services to real estate and
specialty finance related companies. From 1989 to 1991, Mr.&#160;Cohen worked at
Bear Stearns &amp; Co. where he attained the position of Managing Director. From
1983 to 1989, Mr.&#160;Cohen served as first Vice President in the Real Estate
Group of Integrated Resources, Inc. From 1980 to 1983, Mr.&#160;Cohen was an
associate at the law firm of Proskauer Rose Goetz &amp; Mendelsohn.
Mr.&#160;Cohen is a member of the bar in both </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">New York and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Florida</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Joseph&#160;M. Jacobs has been a

May&#160;1998 to August&#160;2001. He co-founded Wexford Capital LLC in 1994 and
serves as its President. From 1982 to 1994, Mr.&#160;Jacobs was employed by Bear
Stearns&#160;&amp; Co.,&#160;Inc. where he attained the position of Senior
Managing Director. From 1979 to 1982, he was employed as a commercial lending
officer at Citibank, N.A. Mr.&#160;Jacobs is a director of several
privately-held companies in which Wexford Capital has an
investment.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Douglas&#160;J. Lambert has been a

to 2003, Mr.&#160;Lambert was a Senior Vice President of Wexford Capital LLC.
From 1983 to 1994, Mr.&#160;Lambert held various financial positions with

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Mark&#160;E. Landesman has been a

Associates, Inc., an entertainment business management firm, which he founded in

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Mark L. Plaumann has been a director
since June 2002. He is presently a Managing-Member of Greyhawke Capital Advisors
LLC, which he co-founded in 1998. From 1995 to 1998, Mr. Plaumann was a Senior
Vice President of Wexford Capital LLC. From 1990 to 1995, Mr. Plaumann was
employed by Alvarez &amp; Marsal, Inc. as a Managing Director. From 1985 to
1990, Mr. Plaumann worked for American Healthcare Management, Inc., where he
attained the position of President. From 1974 to 1985, Mr.&#160;Plaumann worked
in both the audit and consulting divisions of Ernst &amp; Young, where he
attained the position of Senior Manager and he is a certified public
accountant.</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Mr. Plaumann is the Chair of our Audit
Committee, is an &#8220;audit committee financial expert&#8221; and is independent as
defined under applicable SEC and Nasdaq rules.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">On December 3, 2007 Jay L. Maymudes
resigned as a director and committee member of the Company.&#160;&#160;There
were no disagreements with the Company.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Code-Share
Agreements</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Through our subsidiaries, we have
entered into code-share agreements with US Airways, American, Delta, United,
Continental and Frontier that authorize us to use their two-character flight
designator codes (&#8220;US,&#8221; &#8220;AA,&#8221; &#8220;DL,&#8221; &#8220;UA,&#8221; &#8220;CO&#8221; and &#8220;F9&#8221;) to identify our flights
and fares in their computer reservation systems, to paint our aircraft with
their colors and/or logos, to use their service marks and to market and
advertise our status as US Airways Express, AmericanConnection, Delta
Connection, United Express, Continental Express and Frontier Airlines,
respectively. In connection with a marketing agreement among Delta, Continental
and Northwest Airlines, certain of the routes that we fly using Delta's and
Continental&#8217;s flight designator codes are also flown under Northwest's
designator code. Under the code-share agreements between our subsidiaries and
each of US Airways, American, Delta, United, Continental and Frontier, we are
compensated on a fixed-fee basis on all of our US Airways Express,
AmericanConnection, Delta Connection, United Express, Continental Express and
Frontier Airlines flights. In addition, under our code-share agreements, our
passengers participate in frequent flyer programs of the Partners, and the
Partners provide additional services such as reservations, ticket issuance,
ground support services, commuter slot rights and airport
facilities.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">US Airways Code-Share
Agreements</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">We have entered into an Amended and
Restated Jet Services Agreement with US Airways, dated April 26, 2005. The
code-share agreement provides that we will operate these aircraft to provide US
Airways Express service between US Airways hubs and cities designated by US
Airways. On July 21, 2006, we amended this agreement and agreed to remove 20
ERJ-145 aircraft from US Airways operations and transition them into operation
under the Continental code-share agreement during 2007.&#160;&#160;As of
December 31, 2007, all </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">20
aircraft</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> have been
transitioned from US Airways to Continental. As of December 31, 2007, we
operated </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">10 ERJ</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">-145 aircraft under this
agreement.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">In September 2005, w</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">e entered into a code-share agreement
with US Airways to operate 28 ERJ-170 aircraft on terms substantially similar to
those of the ERJ-145 code-share agreement between us and US Airways. On July 24,
2006, we amended this agreement to operate an additional </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">30 ERJ</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">-175 aircraft. The ERJ-175 aircraft have
a term of twelve years for each aircraft. As of December 31, 2007, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">20 </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">of the ERJ-175 aircraft were in service
for US Airways; the remaining </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">10 </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">will be placed into service in
2008.</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;&#160;We further
amended this agreement in</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">
December 2006 to</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> allow us
the option to replace up to eight ERJ-170 aircraft with eight ERJ-175 aircraft.
As of December 31, 2007, we replaced five of the eight, such that, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">23 ERJ</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">-170 and 25 ERJ-175 aircraft were in
operation under this agreement.&#160;&#160;By the end of 2008 we anticipate
having 20 ERJ-170 aircraft and 38 ERJ-175 aircraft in operation under this
agreement.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">In exchange for providing the designated
number of flights and performing our other obligations under the code-share
agreements, we receive compensation from US Airways three times each month in
consideration for the services provided under the code-share agreements. We
receive an additional amount per available seat mile flown and may also receive
incentives or pay penalties based upon our performance, including fleet launch
performance, on-time departure performance and completion percentage rates. In
addition certain of our operating costs are considered "pass through" costs
whereby US Airways has agreed to reimburse us the actual amount of costs we
incur for these items. Landing fees, passenger catering, passenger liability
insurance and aircraft property tax costs are pass through costs and included in
our regional airline services revenue. Beginning in May 2005, US Airways elected
to provide fuel directly for all of our US Airways operations. This change
eliminated fuel expense and the related fuel reimbursement (previously recorded
as revenue). Operating margins were not affected by this
change.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">As of December 31, 2007, we were
providing </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">320
flights</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> per day as US
Airways Express between </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">New
York</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Boston</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Philadelphia</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Pittsburgh</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Indianapolis</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Washington</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, D.C. and designated outlying
cities.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The code-share agreement for the ERJ-145
aircraft terminates in March 2013.&#160;&#160;The code-share agreement for the
ERJ-170 aircraft and the ERJ-175 aircraft terminates in September 2015 with
respect to the ERJ-170 aircraft and twelve years from the in-service date for
each ERJ-175 aircraft. US Airways may terminate the code-share agreements at any
time for cause upon not less than 90 days notice and subject to our right to
cure under the following conditions:</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if we fail to perform or observe any
material covenant or condition or agreement to be performed or observed by us,
provided that if we breach any payment obligation, US Airways has the right to
terminate the agreement on 10 days&#8217; prior written notice unless we cure such
breach prior to the expiration of 10 days;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">-11-</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if our flight completion factor falls
below specified percentages during specified periods due to operational
deficiencies that are within our control;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if our on time departure performance
falls below specified percentages during specified periods;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if we admit liability or are found
liable for any safety infraction by the FAA that could reasonably be expected to
lead to the suspension or revocation of our operating certificate or if in US
Airways' reasonable opinion we are not complying in any material respect with
applicable safety and operational requirements;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if we fail to use commercially
reasonable efforts to comply with the applicable provisions of the &#8220;Jets for
Jobs&#8221; protocol;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if our FAA operating certificate is
suspended or revoked; or</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; in the event that we or an affiliate
of ours shall have commenced the provision of flight services under the code
share between US Airways and Republic Airline and such agreement is subsequently
terminated, among other things.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">In September, 2005, we purchased 113
commuter slots at </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Ronald</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Reagan</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Washington</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">National</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;(DCA) </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Airport and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> 24 commuter slots at New York-LaGuardia
(LGA) Airport under our commuter slot option agreement with US Airways. We
assigned the right of use for these commuter slots to US Airways and these
commuter slots are being operated by US Airways and US Airways Express carriers
under a licensing agreement for which US Airways pays us rent. Prior to the
expiration of the agreement to license the commuter slots, US Airways has the
right to repurchase all, but not less than all, of the </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">DCA commuter</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> slots at a predetermined price. The
licensing agreement between us and US Airways for the LGA commuter slots expired
on December 31, 2006, but we maintain a security interest in the LGA slots if US
Airways fails to perform under the current licensing
agreement.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The American Code-Share
Agreement</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">As of December 31, 2007, we operated
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">15 ERJ</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">-140 aircraft for American under a
fixed-fee code-share agreement and provided 90 flights</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> per day between </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">St. Louis and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> designated outlying
cities.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Under the code-share agreement, American
retains all passenger, certain cargo and other revenues associated with each
flight, and is responsible for all revenue-related expenses. We share revenue
with American for certain cargo shipments. Additionally, certain operating costs
are considered "pass through" costs and American has agreed to reimburse us the
actual amount of costs we incur for these items. Fuel, landing fees, hull and
liability insurance and aircraft property tax costs are pass through costs and
included in our regional airline services&#160;revenue. Aircraft lease payments
are also considered a pass through cost, but are limited to a specified limit
with respect to the first 20 aircraft put into service for American. American
pays us periodically throughout the month on an agreed schedule, subject to
American's right to offset amounts we owe them under the code-share agreement. A
reconciliation payment will be made by American to us if uncontrollable
cancellations exceed a specified level of scheduled block hours during any
calendar quarter.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">If American terminates the code-share
agreement for cause, American has a call option to require that we assign to
American all of its rights under the leases of aircraft, and to lease to
American the aircraft to the extent we own them, used at that time under the
code-share agreement. If American exercises its call option, we are required to
pay certain maintenance costs in transferring the aircraft to American's
maintenance program.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">If American terminates the code-share
agreement without cause, we have the right to put the leases of the aircraft, or
to </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">sell </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">the aircraft to American to the extent
owned by us, used under the code-share agreement to American. American also has
a call option to require us to assign to American these leases. If we exercise
our put or American exercises its call right, both parties are obligated to
implement a schedule to terminate the code-share agreement in an orderly fashion
and transition the aircraft from us to American.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The term of the American code-share
agreement continues until February 1, 2013. American may reduce the term by one
year each time that we fail to achieve an agreed performance level. American may
only exercise this right three times during the term of the code-share
agreement. The agreement may be subject to termination for cause prior to that
date under various circumstances including:</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; a change in the regulations governing
air carriers that materially affects the rights and/or obligations of either
party, subject to negotiation of amendments to the code-share agreement or third
party mediation;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">-12-</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if we or American become insolvent or
fail to pay our debts as they become due, the other party may terminate the
agreement subject to five business days notice and rights of
assurance;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; failure by us or American to perform
the material terms, covenants or conditions of the code-share agreement, which
includes the American standards of service, subject to 30 day notice and cure
rights;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if we or American fail to make a
payment when due, subject to five business days notice and cure
rights;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if either party suspends or is
required to suspend its operations due to any safety reason, the other party may
terminate the agreement on five days notice;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if American, in its reasonable
discretion, determines that we materially breached a representation or warranty
to them that creates a serious and imminent threat to the safe operation of
AmericanConnection services, American may immediately terminate the code-share
agreement;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if we fail to achieve specified levels
of operating performance in completion factor, on-time arrivals, customer
complaints and baggage, American may terminate the agreement, subject to
corrective action plan and adherence to such plan; or</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if either party assigns, by operation
of law or otherwise, the code-share agreement without the written consent of the
other party, subject to five days notice and cure rights, or if we enter into
any merger, sale or acquisition of all or substantially all of our assets or a
majority of our outstanding voting interests with an air carrier other than an
entity that is under common control with us.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">American may terminate the code-share
agreement without cause upon 180 days notice, provided that such notice may not
be given prior to September 30, 2008. If American exercises this right, it is
required to reimburse us for certain costs and we and American have certain
"put" and "call" rights with respect to the aircraft we operate for
them.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">If American terminates the code-share
agreement for any reason prior to September 30, 2008, or we terminate the
code-share agreement prior to September 30, 2008, due to a breach of the
agreement by American, American has agreed to reimburse us for certain price
concessions that we granted American.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The Delta Code-Share
Agreements</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">In March 2007, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">we amended</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">our</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">fixed-fee agreements with Delta. On
March 27, 2007 the United States Bankruptcy Court for the Southern District of
New York approved the amended agreements. Key terms of the amended agreements
include the removal of all 15 ERJ-135 aircraft beginning in September 2008 at a
rate of two aircraft per month, and effective May 1, 2007, an approximate 3%
permanent reduction of block hour fees charged on </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">our remaining</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> 24 ERJ-145 and </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">our 16</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> ERJ-170 aircraft.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">On August
22, 2007, we amended our Jet Services Agreement with Delta to provide for the
replacement of 16 ERJ-170 regional aircraft operating as Delta Connection with
16 ERJ-175 regional jet aircraft.&#160;&#160;The new aircraft are expected to be
placed into service during the second half of 2008 and the first quarter of
2009.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">As of December 31, 2007, we operated 15
ERJ-135 aircraft, 24 ERJ-145 aircraft, including two spares, and 16 ERJ-170
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">aircraft for Delta under
fixed-fee code-share agreements. As of December 31, 2007, we provided 330
flights</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> per day as Delta
Connection between </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Cincinnati</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Columbus and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Atlanta and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> designated outlying cities. In
connection with a marketing agreement among Delta, Continental and Northwest
Airlines, certain of the routes that we fly using Delta's and Continental&#8217;s
flight designator codes are also flown under Northwest's designator
code.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The code-share agreements for the
ERJ-145 and ERJ-170 aircraft terminate in May 2016 and January 2019,
respectively. Delta may terminate the code-share agreements at any time, with or
without cause, if it provides us 180 days written notice, provided that such
notice shall not be given prior to November 2009</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> for the ERJ-145 regional jet code-share
agreement and </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">July
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">2015 for</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> the ERJ-170 regional jet code-share
agreement.&#160;&#160;If Delta does choose to eliminate any aircraft at that
time, it may not reduce the number of aircraft in service to less than 12 during
the 12-month period following the 180 day initial notice period unless it
completely terminates the code-share agreement. We refer to this as Delta's
partial termination right.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">If Delta exercises this right under
either agreement or if we terminate either agreement for cause, we have the
right to require Delta either to purchase, sublease or assume the lease of
aircraft leased by us with respect to any of the aircraft we previously operated
for Delta under that agreement. If we choose not to exercise this right, or if
Delta terminates either agreement for cause, Delta may require us to sell or
sublease to it or Delta may assume the lease of aircraft leased by us with
respect to any of the aircraft we previously operated for it under that
agreement.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">-13-</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Certain of our operating costs are
considered "pass through" costs, whereby Delta has agreed to reimburse us the
actual amount of costs we incur for these items. Fuel, engine maintenance
expenses, landing fees, passenger liability insurance, hull insurance, war risk
insurance, de-icing costs, and aircraft property taxes are some of the pass
through costs and included in our regional airline services revenue. Aircraft
rent/ownership expenses are also considered a pass through cost, but the
reimbursement is limited to specified amounts for certain
aircraft.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The initial term of the ERJ-145
code-share agreement is until May 31, 2016. At the end of the term, Delta has
the right to extend the agreement for an additional five years on the same terms
and conditions. If either we or Chautauqua enter into a merger where we are not
the surviving entity or the ultimate beneficial ownership of the surviving
entity following a merger is not substantially similar (i.e., at least 75%
common ownership) to the ultimate beneficial ownership of us or Chautauqua prior
to the merger (which we refer to as a merger), or if a party acquires more than
49% of our voting power or outstanding common stock or that of Chautauqua (with
limited exceptions) (which we refer to as a change in control), Delta shall have
the right to extend the term of the code-share agreement for an additional ten
years beyond the applicable termination date of the
agreement.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The agreement may be subject to early
termination under various circumstances including:</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if either Delta or we file for
bankruptcy, reorganization or similar action (or if any such action is imminent)
or if either Delta or we make an assignment for the benefit of
creditors;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if either Delta or we commit a
material breach of the code-share agreement, subject to 30 days notice and cure
rights; or</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; upon the occurrence of an event of
force majeure that continues for a period of two or more consecutive months,
subject to 30 days prior written notice to the party affected by the force
majeure event.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">In addition, Delta may immediately
terminate the code-share agreement upon the occurrence of one or more of the
following events:</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if there is a change in control of
us;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if there is a merger involving
us;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if Delta is unsatisfied with the
product quality we are providing 30 days after it has supplied us written notice
of its dissatisfaction and has proposed remedial measures;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if we fail to maintain a specified
completion rate with respect to the flights we operate for Delta during a
specified period; or</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8226; if our level of safety is not
reasonably satisfactory to Delta, subject to 30 days notice and cure
period.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The United Code-Share
Agreements</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">On August 22, 2007, we </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">amended</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> our Jet Services Agreement with United
to provide for the operation of </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">ten additional</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> ERJ-170 aircraft as United Express. The
aircraft</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, which will
transition from Delta, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">are
expected to be placed into service during the fourth quarter of 2008 and the
first quarter of 2009.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;We have entered into fixed-fee
code-share agreements with United to operate </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">seven ERJ-145 aircraft and 38 ERJ-170
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">aircraft to provide United
Express Service in markets to be determined by United. As of December 31, 2007,
we operated </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">seven ERJ-145
aircraft and 28 ERJ</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">-170
aircraft and provided </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">200
flights</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> per day as United
Express between Chicago, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Washington</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">D.C. </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">and designated outlying
cities.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The fixed rates that we receive from
United under the code-share agreements are annually adjusted in accordance with
an agreed escalation formula. Additionally, certain of our operating costs are
considered "pass through" costs whereby United has agreed to reimburse us the
actual amount of costs we incur for these items. Fuel and oil, landing fees, war
risk insurance, liability insurance and aircraft property taxes are pass through
costs and included in our regional airline services revenue.</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;&#160;Beginning in January 2007,
United elected to provide fuel directly in certain locations, which eliminates a
portion of our fuel expense and the related fuel reimbursement (previously
recorded as revenue).</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The ERJ-145 and ERJ-170 code-share
agreements terminate on June 30, 2014 and June 30, 2019, respectively. United
has the option of extending each agreement for five years or less; however, the
ERJ-145 code-share agreement may be terminated by United </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">or us </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">upon 18 months prior written notice
provided that such notice shall not be delivered </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">by United </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">prior to December 31, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">2007, and&#160;&#160;by us prior to
December 31, 2008</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">. In
addition, the code-share agreements may be terminated under the following
conditions:</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
