      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(1)&#160;Two of these aircraft are used
for charter operations and as spares at December 31, 2006,
2005.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(2) Two of these aircraft </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">were </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">used for charter operations and as
spares at December 31, 2006</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.&#160;&#160;One of these aircraft were
used for charter operations and as spares at December 31, 2007 and </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">2005.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(3) Four of these aircraft </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">were unassigned </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">at December 31, 200</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">6.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">In addition to the aircraft listed
above, we subleased </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">six
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">ERJ-145 aircraft to an
airline in </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Mexico</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">During 1999, we began operating Embraer
aircraft on behalf of US Airways under a fixed-fee arrangement. There were 58,
58 and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">40 Embraer aircraft operating on behalf
of US Airways at December&#160;31, 2007, 2006 and 2005, respectively. During
2000, we began operations on behalf of TWA under a fixed-fee arrangement; TWA
was subsequently acquired by American. There were </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">15 Embraer</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> aircraft operating under the agreement
with American at December&#160;31, 2007, 2006 and 2005. At December&#160;31,
2007, 2006 and&#160;2005, respectively, we had 55, 55 and </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">48 aircraft in operation under our
agreements with Delta. We began operations for United in June 2004, and at
December 31, 2007, 2006 and 2005 respectively, we had 35 Embraer aircraft in
operation under the agreement with United.&#160;&#160;In January 2007 we began
operations for Continental, and at December 31, 2007 we had </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">20 Embraer and 24 Bombardie</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">r regional jet aircraft in operation
with Continental. In March 2007 we began operations for Frontier, and at
December 31, 2007 we had nine</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">aircraft in operation with
Frontier.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Revenue</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Under our fixed-fee arrangements with
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">our Partners</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, we receive fixed-fee</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">s</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, as well as reimbursement of specified
costs on a gross basis with additional possible incentives from our Partners for
superior performance. For the years ended December&#160;31, 2007, 2006 and 2005
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">all of</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> our regional airline services revenue
was earned under our fixed-fee arrangements. </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The number</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> of aircraft we operate and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> aircraft utilization are the most
significant drivers of our revenue</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, as opposed to the number of passengers
we carry or</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> the fare the
passengers pay.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Operating Expenses</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">A brief description of the items
included in our operating expenses line items follows.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Wages and Benefits</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">This expense includes not only wages and
salaries, but also expenses associated with various employee benefit plans,
employee incentives and payroll taxes. These expenses will fluctuate based
primarily on our level of operations </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">changes in wage rates for contract and
non-contract employees and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">
changes in costs of our benefit plans</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Aircraft Fuel</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Fuel expense includes the cost of
aircraft fuel, including fuel taxes and into-plane fees.&#160; </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Beginning in May 2005, we do not record
fuel expense and the related revenue for US Airways operations because US
Airways pays for fuel directly.&#160;&#160;Beginning in January 2007, for
certain United locations, we do not record fuel expense and the related revenue
because United pays for fuel directly. Continental and Frontier pay fuel
directly and their operations began in January and March 2007,
respectively.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">-35-</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Landing Fees</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">This expense consists of fees charged by
airports for each aircraft landing.&#160;&#160; </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Under our current fixed-fee agreements,
we are reimbursed for the actual costs of landing fees.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Aircraft and Engine
Rent</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">This expense consists of the costs of
leasing aircraft and spare engines. The leased aircraft and spare engines are
operated under long-term operating leases with third parties. The lease payments
associated with future aircraft deliveries are subject to market conditions for
interest rates and contractual price increases for the aircraft. Aircraft rent
is reduced by the amortization of integration funding credits received from the
aircraft manufacturer for parts and training. The credits are amortized on a
straight-line basis over the term of the respective lease of the
aircraft.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Maintenance and
Repair</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Maintenance and repair expenses include
all parts, materials, tooling and spares required to maintain our aircraft. We
have entered into long-term maintenance "power-by-the-hour" service contracts
with third-party maintenance providers under which we are charged fixed rates
for each flight hour accumulated by </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">all </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">of our engines and some of the major
airframe components. The effect of such contracts is to reduce the volatility of
aircraft maintenance expense over the term of the contract.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Insurance and Taxes</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">This expense includes the costs of
passenger liability insurance, aircraft hull insurance, war risk insurance and
all other insurance policies, other than employee welfare insurance.
Additionally, this expense includes personal and real property taxes, including
aircraft property taxes. Under our current fixed-fee agreements, we are
reimbursed for the actual costs of passenger liability insurance, war risk
insurance, aircraft hull insurance and property taxes, subject to certain
restrictions. Under our US Airways and United fixed-fee agreements, we are
reimbursed for the actual costs of such items other than aircraft hull
insurance, which is reimbursed at agreed upon rates.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Depreciation and
Amortization</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;This expense includes the
depreciation of all fixed assets, including aircraft, and the amortization of
the commuter slots that we own.&#160; Goodwill and intangibles with an
indefinite life are required to be evaluated for impairment on an annual basis.
If we determine the goodwill and intangibles are impaired, we are required to
write-off the amount of goodwill and intangibles that are impaired.&#160; As of
December 31, 2007 and 2006, goodwill and intangibles was </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">$62.0 million</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> and $62.4 million respectively, net of
amortization.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Other</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">This expense includes the costs of crew
training, crew travel, airport, passenger and ground handling related expenses,
all other lease expense</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">s</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, professional fees and all other
administrative, facilities and operational overhead expenses not included in
other line items above.&#160;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(1) </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Beginning in May 2005, we do not record
fuel expense and the related revenue for US Airways operations because US
Airways pays for fuel directly.&#160;&#160;Beginning in January 2007, for
certain United locations, we do not record fuel expense and the related revenue
because United pays for fuel directly. Continental and Frontier pay fuel
directly and their operations began in January and March 2007,
respectively.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(2)&#160;In 2005, we reversed a $4.2
million reserve after an agreement to return all the Saab turboprop aircraft to
lessors was executed and all liabilities were settled. In 2006, we recorded a
$2.1 million gain relating to the disposition of Saab aircraft and spare
parts.</font></font></div>

                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">219</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td align="left" valign="bottom" width="1%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
              </td>
              <td align="left" valign="bottom" width="1%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
              </td>
              <td align="right" valign="bottom" width="7%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">28.1</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td align="left" valign="bottom" width="2%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">%</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td align="left" valign="bottom" width="1%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
              </td>
              <td align="right" valign="bottom" width="10%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">171</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td align="left" valign="bottom" width="1%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>

              <td align="left" valign="bottom" width="1%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
              </td>
              <td align="right" valign="bottom" width="6%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">20.4</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td align="left" valign="bottom" width="2%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">%</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td align="left" valign="bottom" width="1%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>

              <td align="right" valign="bottom" width="10%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">142</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td align="left" valign="bottom" width="1%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(1)&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">P</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">assenger</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">s carried multiplied by </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">miles </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">flown</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(2)&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Passenger seats a</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">vailable multiplied by </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">miles </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">flown.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(3)&#160;Revenue passenger miles divided
by available seat miles.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(4)&#160;Total operating and interest
expenses divided by available seat miles.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(5)&#160;Cost of aircraft fuel,
including fuel taxes and into-plane fees.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(6) </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Beginning in May 2005, we do not record
fuel expense and the related revenue for US Airways operations because US
Airways pays for fuel directly.&#160;&#160;Beginning in January 2007, for
certain United locations, we do not record fuel expense and the related revenue
because United pays for fuel directly. Continental and Frontier pay fuel
directly and their operations began in January and March 2007,
respectively.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(7)&#160;Hours from takeoff to landing,
including taxi time.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(8)&#160;Average number of hours per day
that an aircraft flown in revenue service is operated (from gate departure to
gate arrival).</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;&#160;</font></font></div><br>

                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 6.3pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">7.61</font></font></div>
              </td>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(1)&#160; In 2006, we recorded a $2.1
million gain relating to the disposition of Saab aircraft and spare
parts.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Operating revenue in 2007 increased by
13.1%, or $149.6&#160;million, to $1.29 billion compared to $1.14&#160;billion
in 2006. </font>Excluding reimbursement for fuel expense, which is a
pass-through cost to our Partners, regional airline service revenues increased
23.4% for 2007.&#160;&#160;<font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The
increase was due primarily to fixed-fee revenue earned from </font>the addition
of 49 regional jet aircraft that were placed into service throughout 2007 and
one regional jet aircraft removed from charter service and subleased to an
airline in Mexico during 2007<font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.
Other operating revenue decreased $3.7 million due to a decrease in payments
from US Airways for the use of aircraft take-off and landing slots at LaGuardia
airport, which expired at the end of 2006.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Total operating and interest expenses,
excluding fuel increased by 25.4%, or $177.0 million, to $873.1&#160;million for
2007 compared to $696.1 million during 2006 due to the increase in flight
operations. The cost per available seat mile on total operating and interest
expenses, excluding fuel charges, decreased to 7.58&#162; in 2007 compared to 7.61&#162;
in 2006. Factors relating to the change in operating expenses are discussed
below.&#160;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Wages and benefits increased by 29.1%,
or $51.0&#160;million, to $226.5&#160;million for 2007 compared to $175.5
million for 2006 due primarily to a $34.1 million increase in flight crew and
maintenance operations wage expenses to support the increase in regional jet
operations, a $12.7 million increase in related payroll</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> taxes and increased employment levels
and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> an increase in stock
compensation expense recognition of $1.8 million, to $3.1 million in 2007. The
cost per available seat mile increased to 1.97&#162; for 2007 compared to 1.92&#162; in
2006.&#160;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Aircraft fuel expense decreased 8.9%, or
$28.9 million, to&#160;$296.6 million for 2007 compared to $325.5&#160;million
for 2006 due to a 17<font style="COLOR: #000000">% </font></font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">decrease in gallons consumed due to
United paying for fuel directly for certain locations beginning in January 2007,
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"><font style="COLOR: #000000">partially </font>offset by a 1</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">1</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">% increase in the average fuel price per
gallon from $2.16 in</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> 2006
to $2.40 in 2007.&#160; The unit cost decreased to 2.58&#162; in 2007 compared to
3.55&#162; in 2006.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">-39-</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Landing fees increased by 27.8%, or
$11.7&#160;million, to $53.7&#160;million in 2007 compared to $42.0&#160;million
in 2006. The increase is due mainly to a 16% increase in departures</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, a 3% increase in the average landing
weight and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> a 7% increase in
the average fee charged by airports. Our fixed-fee agreements provide for a
direct reimbursement of landing fees. The unit cost was 0.47&#162; in 2007 compared
to 0.46&#162; in 2006.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Aircraft and engine rent increased by
31.9%, or $30.2&#160;million, to $125.0 million in 2007 compared to
$94.8&#160;million in 2006 due to a $22.2 million increase in aircraft rents of
CRJ-200 aircraft, which are on short-term leases and an $11.1 million increase
in aircraft rents of 70-seat aircraft, and is partially offset by the effect of
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">the purchase of five
previously leased 50</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">-seat
aircraft in the third quarter of 2006.&#160;&#160;The unit cost increased to
1.0</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">8</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#162; for 2007 compared to 1.03&#162; for
2006.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Maintenance and repair expenses
increased by 23.8%, or $25.0 million, to $130.2 million in 2007 compared to
$105.2 million for 2006&#160;due mainly to the addition of 49 aircraft in 2007,
which resulted in a $16.6 million increase in long-term maintenance agreement
expenses.&#160;&#160;Additionally, repair expenses on parts not under warranty
or </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">not </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">included under long term contracts
increased $5.6 million.&#160;&#160;Scheduled heavy maintenance events also
increased by $1.2 million.&#160;&#160;The unit cost was down slightly to 1.13&#162;
in 2007 compared to 1.15&#162; in 2006.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Insurance and taxes increased 7.9%, or
$1.4&#160;million, to $19.0&#160;million in 2007 compared to $17.7&#160;million
in 2006. Property taxes increased $1.7 million and the increase in operations
was more than offset by a decline in the average insurance rates year over. Our
fixed-fee agreements generally provide for a direct reimbursement of insurance
and property taxes.&#160;&#160;The unit cost decreased to 0.1</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">6</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#162; in 2007 compared to 0.19&#162; in
2006.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Depreciation and amortization increased
15.6%, or $14.4&#160;million, to&#160;$106.6 million in 2007 compared to
$92.2&#160;million in 2006 due mainly to $15.2 million of additional
depreciation on regional jet aircraft due to the purchase of 11 aircraft in 2007
and the full year effect of 16 regional jet aircraft purchased in 2006.
Additionally, amortization for takeoff and landing slots decreased $3.3 million
from 2006 due to slots at LaGuardia airport expiring at the end of 2006. The
unit cost decreased to 0.93&#162; in 2007 compared to 1.01&#162; in
2006.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Impairment loss and accrued return costs
was a ($2.1) million benefit in 2006, which represented the gain on the
disposition of Saab aircraft and spare parts.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Other expenses increased 31.5%, or $25.1
million, to $104.8 million in 2007 from $79.7 million in 2006, due primarily to
$15.8 million of increases in flight crew training and travel expenses and $7.6
million of increases in passenger catering costs and other operational expenses
to support the increased regional jet operations and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> increased pilot attrition</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">. The unit cost increased to 0.91&#162; in
2007 compared to 0.87&#162; in 2006.&#160;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Interest expense increased 17.8% or
$16.2&#160;million, to $107.3&#160;million in 2007 from $91.1 million in 2006
primarily due to interest on debt related to the financing of 11 aircraft during
2007 and the full year effect of 16 regional jet aircraft financed in 2006. The
weighted average interest rate remained constant at 6.2%. The unit cost
decreased to 0.93&#162; in 2007 compared to 1.00&#162; in 2006.&#160;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">We incurred income tax expense of $51.2
million during 2007, compared to $51.9 million in 2006. The effective tax rates
for 2007 and 2006 were 38.2% and 39.5%, respectively, which were higher than the
statutory rate due to state income taxes and non-deductible meals and
entertainment expense, primarily for our flight crews.&#160;&#160;In
addition</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">during the fourth quarter of 2007 the
Company reduced its estimated blended state tax rate based on its current
operations.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div><br>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">2006 Compared to
2005</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>

                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 6.95pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">8.10</font></font></div>
              </td>
              <td valign="bottom" width="1%" style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4px"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(1)&#160; In 2005, we reversed a $4.2
million reserve after an agreement to return all the Saab turboprop aircraft to
lessors was executed and all liabilities were settled. In 2006, we recorded a
$2.1 million gain relating to the disposition of Saab aircraft and spare
parts.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Operating revenue in 2006 increased by
26.3%, or $238.1&#160;million, to $1.1 billion compared to $905.0&#160;million
in 2005. The increase was due primarily to fixed-fee revenue earned from
twenty-nine 70-seat aircraft added to revenue service in 2006. Eighteen aircraft
were added for US Airways, seven were added for Delta, and four were placed on
short-term assignment in late 2006 with current Partners and will begin service
for Frontier in the spring of 2007. Other operating revenue increased $6.4
million due to a full year of sublease revenue on aircraft and payments from US
Airways for the use of aircraft take-off and landing slots in 2006 which we
began recording in September 2005.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Total operating expenses increased by
24.7%, or $184.2 million, to $930.5 million in 2006 compared to $746.3 million
in 2005 due to the increase in flight operations. Total operating and interest
expenses increased by 26.2%, or $211.9 million, to $1,021.6&#160;million for
2006 compared to $809.8 million during 2005 due to the increase in flight
operations. The cost per available seat mile on total operating and interest
expenses, excluding fuel charges, decreased to 7.6&#162; in 2006 compared to 8.1&#162; in
2005. Factors relating to the change in operating expenses are discussed
below.&#160;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Wages and benefits increased by 22.0%,
or $31.7&#160;million, to $175.5&#160;million for 2006 compared to $143.8 due
primarily to a $25.3 million increase in flight crew and maintenance operations
wage expenses to support the increase in 70-seat regional jet operations and a
$8.7 million increase in related employee benefit costs resulting from the
additional wage expense and stock compensation expense recognition of $1.3
million in 2006. These increases were partially offset by a $4.4 million
decrease in the wage expense for Customer Service employees due to the
elimination of ground handling operations for American in </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">St. Louis in</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> March 2006. The cost per available seat
mile decreased to 1.9&#162; for 2006 compared to 2.2&#162; in
2005.&#160;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Aircraft fuel expense increased 16.7%,
or $46.6 million, to&#160;$325.5 million for 2006 compared to
$278.9&#160;million for 2005 due to a 10% increase in the average fuel price per
gallon and a 6% increase in gallons consumed. Beginning in May 2005, we no
longer record fuel expense and the related revenue for US Airways operations
because US Airways pays for fuel directly. The average price per gallon was
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">$2.1</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">6 </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">in 2006 and $1.98 in 2005</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.&#160; The unit cost decreased to 3.6&#162;
in 2006 compared to 4.3&#162; in 2005 due to the increase in the 70-seat US Airways
operations, for which no fuel expense is recorded.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">-41-</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Landing fees increased by 38.2%, or
$11.6&#160;million, to $42.0&#160;million in 2006 compared to $30.4&#160;million
in 2005. The increase is due to a 16% increase in departures and a 17% increase
in the average landing weight resulting from the increase in 70-seat operations
in 2006. Our fixed-fee agreements provide for a direct reimbursement of landing
fees. The unit cost remained unchanged at 0.5&#162;.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Aircraft and engine rent increased by
21.9%, or $17.0&#160;million, to $94.8 million in 2006 compared to
$77.7&#160;million in 2005 due to a $22.4 million increase in aircraft rents of
70-seat aircraft resulting from the additional leases of fifteen 70-seat
aircraft in 2006, and is partially offset by the effect of buying out five
50-seat aircraft in the third quarter of 2006 and removing the final seven
turboprop aircraft from lease in the fourth quarter of 2005. The unit cost
decreased to 1.0&#162; for 2006 compared to 1.2&#162; for 2005.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Maintenance and repair expenses
increased by 37.6%, or $28.7 million, to $105.2 million in 2006 compared to
$76.5 million for 2005&#160;due mainly to a $29.6 million increase in 70-seat
regional jet maintenance expenses resulting from the increase in 70-seat
operations in 2006. Additionally, maintenance expenses on our smaller jets
(37-50 seats) increased $5.4 million over 2005 due mainly to contractual rate
increases on certain of our engines under a long-term maintenance agreement,
which are reimbursed as pass-through expenses. The increase in regional jet
expenses was partially offset by a decrease of $6.4 million from 2005 turboprop
maintenance expenses as a result of the removal of the turboprops. The unit cost
remained unchanged at 1.2&#162;.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Insurance and taxes increased 9.5%, or
$1.5&#160;million, to $17.7&#160;million in 2006 compared to $16.1&#160;million
in 2005. The increase in operations was mostly offset by a decline in the
average insurance rates year over year and a $0.4 million decrease in aircraft
property taxes. The unit cost decreased to 0.2&#162; for 2006 compared to 0.3&#162; in
2005.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Depreciation and amortization increased
42.2%, or $27.4&#160;million, to&#160;$92.2 million in 2006 compared to
$64.9&#160;million in 2005 due mainly to $24.1 million of additional
depreciation on regional jet aircraft due to the purchase of 16 aircraft in 2006
and the full year effect of 31 regional jet aircraft purchased in 2005.
Additionally, amortization for takeoff and landing slots increased $2.8 million
from 2005. The unit cost remained unchanged at 1.0&#162;.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Impairment loss and accrued return costs
was a ($2.1) million benefit in 2006 compared to ($4.2) million benefit in 2005.
The ($2.1) million in 2006 represent the gain on the disposition of Saab
aircraft and spare parts. The ($4.2) million in 2005 was the reversal of the
remaining balance of a reserve for the return of our Saab fleet of aircraft
after an agreement to return all the Saab turboprop aircraft to lessors was
executed and all liabilities were settled.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Other expenses increased 28.2%, or $17.5
million, to $79.7 million in 2006 from $62.2 million in 2005, due primarily to
$22.5 million of increases in flight crew training and travel expenses,
passenger catering costs, and administrative expenses to support the increased
70-seat regional jet operations, offset by a decrease of $6.3 million in
payments made to American in 2005 related to operating 70-seat aircraft at
Chautauqua. The unit cost remained unchanged at 0.9&#162;.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Interest expense increased 43.4% or
$27.6&#160;million, to $91.1&#160;million in 2006 from $63.5 million in 2005
primarily due to interest on debt related to the financing of 16 aircraft during
2006 and the full year effect of 31 regional jet aircraft financed in 2005. The
weighted average interest rate increased to 6.1% in 2006 from 5.6% in 2005. The
unit cost remained unchanged at 1.0&#162;.&#160;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">We incurred income tax expense of $51.9
million during 2006, compared to $39.5 million in 2005. The effective tax rates
for 2006 and 2005 were 39.5% and 39.5%, respectively, which were higher than the
statutory rate due to state income taxes and non-deductible meals and
entertainment expense, primarily for our flight crews.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Liquidity and Capital
Resources</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">As of December 31, 2007, we had
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">$164.0 million</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> in cash and </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">$2.5 million</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> available under our revolving credit
facility. At December 31, 2007, we had a working capital deficiency of
$(</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">23.0</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">) million.&#160;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;&#160;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">In March 2007, the Company&#8217;s revolving
credit facility with</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> Bank
of America Business Capital was amended extending the term to March 31, 2009 and
providing a revolving credit facility of $15.0 million.&#160;&#160;The revolving
credit facility allows the Company to borrow up to 30% of the lower of net book
value or appraised orderly liquidation value of spare rotable parts and up to
15% of the lower of net book value or appraised orderly liquidation value of
spare non-rotable parts for our regional jet fleet. The revolving credit
facility is collateralized by all of the Company&#8217;s assets, excluding the owned
aircraft and engines. The revolving credit facility terminated future equipment
loans and reduced the spare parts borrowing base. The amendment added a
liquidity covenant to the existing specified fixed charge coverage ratio and a
debt to earnings leverage ratio covenants. The Company pays an annual commitment
fee on the unused portion of the revolving credit facility in an amount equal to
0.375% of the unused amounts. The credit facility limits the Company&#8217;s ability
to incur indebtedness or create or incur liens on its assets. The Company was in
compliance with the covenant at December 31, 2007.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
          </div>

          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">-42-</font></div>

      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">At December 31, 2007, the Company had
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">$12.5</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;million of outstanding letters of
credit.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">During 2007, the Company acquired 22
aircraft through debt financing totaling $438.3 million. The debt was obtained
from banks and the aircraft manufacturer for 12 to 15 year terms </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">at interest rates ranging from
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">6.22% to 7.28%</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">As of December 31, 2007, we leased nine
spare regional jet engines from General Electric Capital Aviation Services,
five&#160;spare regional jet engines from RRPF Engine Leasing (US) LLC and eight
regional jet engines from Miyabi Engine Leasing. </font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Net cash from operating activities was
$170.9 million, $229.1 and $280.5 million for the years ended December&#160;31,
2005, 2006 and 2007, respectively. The increase from operating activities is
primarily due to the continued growth of our business. For 2007, net cash from
operating activities is primarily net income of $82.7 million, depreciation and
amortization of $106.6 million, the change in deferred income taxes of
$51.1&#160;million, the Delta pre-petition claim of $44.6 million partially
offset by </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">in</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">creases of $11.4 million in inventories.
For 2006, net cash from operating activities is primarily net income of $79.5
million, depreciation and amortization of $92.2 million, the change in deferred
income taxes of $51.4&#160;million, the increase in accrued liabilities of
$16.8&#160;million partially offset by increases of $11.4 million in
inventories. For 2005, net cash from operating activities is primarily net
income of $60.7 million, depreciation and amortization of $68.0 million, the
change in deferred income taxes of $37.6&#160;million and the increase in
accrued liabilities of $29.0&#160;million.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Net cash </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">from investing</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> activities was $(175.2) million,
$(114.5) million and $(76.5) million for the years ended December&#160;31, 2005,
2006 and 2007, respectively. In 2007, we purchased 22 regional jet aircraft. Net
aircraft deposits decreased $7.3 million in 2007. Net aircraft deposits
increased</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font>$43.4<font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #ff0000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">million in 2006. In 2005, we purchased
35 aircraft and paid $51.6 million for commuter slots.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Net cash from financing activities was
$120.1 million, $(81.1) million and $(235.5) million for the years ended
December&#160;31, 2005, 2006 and 2007, respectively. In 2007 we made debt
payments of $93.5 million and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> repurchased $142</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.4 million </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">of our common stock.&#160;&#160;In 2006
we made debt payments of $79.9 million.</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">In 2005 we completed two follow on
public stock offering providing $186.8 million and made debt payments of $53.4
million.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic"><font style="BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffff00"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; BACKGROUND-COLOR: white">During
2007, we purchased 7,066,894 shares of our common stock on the market or through
privately negotiated transactions at a weighted average purchase price of $20.15
for total consideration of $142.4 million. We purchased 4,555,000 of these
shares through four privately negotiated transactions with our former majority
shareholder, WexAir RJET LLC, for total consideration of $132.1
million.</font></font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; BACKGROUND-COLOR: white">In
December 2007, our Board of Directors authorized the purchase of up to $100
million of our common stock. The shares will be purchased on the open market or
through privately negotiated transactions from time-to-time during the twelve
month period following the authorization. Under the authorization, the timing
and amount of purchase would be based on market conditions, securities law
limitations and other factors. The stock buy-back program does not obligate us
to acquire any specific number of shares in any period, and may be modified,
suspended, extended or discontinued at any time without prior notice. At
December 31, 2007, the amount under this authorization was $98.6
million</font></div>
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">We
currently anticipate that our available cash resources, cash generated from
operations and anticipated third party funding arrangements will be sufficient
to meet our anticipated working capital and capital expenditure requirements for
at least the next 12 months.</font></div>
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Aircraft Leases and Other Off-Balance
Sheet Arrangements</font></font></div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">We have significant obligations for
aircraft and engines that are classified as operating leases and, therefore, are
not reflected as liabilities on our balance sheet. Aircraft leases expire
between </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">2009 and
2023</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">. As of December 31,
2007, our total mandatory payments under operating leases for aircraft
aggregated approximately </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">$1.1</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;billion and total minimum annual
aircraft rental payments for the next 12&#160;months under all non-cancelable
operating leases is approximately $</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">138.7 </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">million.&#160;Other non-cancelable
operating leases consist of engines, terminal space, operating facilities,
office space and office equipment. The leases expire through </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">2026</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">. As of December 31, 2007, our total
mandatory payments under other non-cancelable operating leases aggregated
approximately $</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">133.1&#160;million. Total minimum annual
other rental payments for the next 12&#160;months are approximately $12.2
million. </font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Purchase Commitments</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">As of December 31, 2007, the Company had
firm orders to purchase </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">29
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">ERJ-170/175 aircraft. The
current total list price of the 29 aircraft is </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">$899 </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">million. During the year ended December
31, 2007, the Company made aircraft deposits in accordance with the aircraft
commitments of $</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">5</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">1.4 million</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">. The Company also has a commitment to
acquire </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">nine
spare</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> aircraft engines with
a current list price of approximately </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">$40.5 </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">million. These commitments are subject
to customary closing conditions.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">In January 2007, the Company and
Frontier entered into an agreement, whereby, Republic will operate for Frontier
17 ERJ-170 aircraft. </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Nine
of</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> the 17 aircraft are
currently in service and the remaining eight aircraft will be transitioned from
our current Partners.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">We expect to fund future capital
commitments through internally generated funds, third-party aircraft financings,
and debt and other financings.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
          </div>
        </div>

available cash resources, cash generated from operations and anticipated
third-party financing arrangements will be sufficient to meet our anticipated
working capital and capital expenditure requirements for at least the next
12&#160;months. We may need to raise additional funds, however, to fund more
rapid expansion, principally the acquisition of additional aircraft, or meet
unanticipated working capital requirements. It is possible that future funding
may not be available to us on favorable terms, or at all.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
