      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">-66-</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: black" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Warrants</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">In connection with the Delta code-share
agreement, the Company had issued warrants to purchase shares of its common
stock related to the code-share agreement. Warrants issued were accounted for
under SFAS No. 123 and E</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">IT</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">F 96-18, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic">Accounting for
Equity Instruments That Are Issued to Other Than Employees for Acquiring, or in
Conjunction with Selling, Goods or Services</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, at fair value on the measurement date.
Accordingly, there was no impact on the accounting for warrants from the
adoption of SFAS 123(R).</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The Company recorded deferred warrant
charges on the measurement date based upon an option pricing model that
considered continuous compounding of dividends and dilution using an estimated
fair value of the Company&#8217;s common stock on the grant date, an estimated
dividend yield, a risk-free interest rate commensurate with the warrant term,
volatility of 40% and an expected life of 10 years. </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Amortization of deferred warrant charges
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">was </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">$</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">0, $</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">565 and </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">$372 for the years ended December 31,
200</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">7</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, 2006 and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> 200</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">5</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, respectively.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">In March 2007, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">the Company amended</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">its</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">fixed-fee </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">code-share </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">agreements with Delta. </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">As a part of this amendment</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, Delta agreed to surrender its warrants
for 3,435,000 shares of the Company&#8217;s common stock</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.&#160;&#160;T</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">he Company recorded a deferred gain on
the surrender of the warrants from Delta of $42,735, which was net of the
write-off of the previously reported unamortized deferred warrant charge of
$6,369. Stockholders' equity was reduced by $</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">32,892</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, net of tax, resulting from the
surrender of the warrants and their retirement. The deferred </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">credits for the proceeds of the
pre-petition claim and the gain on</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> the surrender of the warrants totaling
$87,325&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">is
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">being amortized</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> as an adjustment to revenue over the
weighted</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> average aircraft
in service during the term </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">of the agreements with
Delta.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">11. INCOME TAXES</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The components of the provision for
income tax expense for the years ended December&#160;31 are as
follows:</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">&#160;</div>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The Company adopted the
provision</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">s of
FASB</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> Interpretation No. 48,
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic">Accounting for
Uncertainty in Income Taxes &#8211; An Interpretation of FASB 109 </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(FIN&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">48).&#160;&#160;The Company adopted the
provisions of FIN&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">48
on January 1, 2007.&#160;&#160;The total amount of unrecognized tax benefits as
of the date of the adoption was $3,5</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">15</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, of which the Company had previously
recorded $1,</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">148
for</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> income tax
contingencies prior to adoption.&#160;&#160;Accordingly, the Company recognized
a $2,367 increase</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> in the
liability for the unrecognized tax benefits which was accounted for as a
reduction to retained earnings and an increase to deferred tax
liability.&#160;&#160;During the year ended December 31, 2007, the Company
recognized approximately $894 additional tax expense for unrecognized tax
benefits.&#160;&#160;All of the unrecognized tax benefits as of December 31,
2007, if recognized, would affect the effective tax rate.&#160;&#160;The Company
monitors ongoing tax cases related to its unrecognized tax
benefits.&#160;&#160;If an unfavorable tax case judgment is rendered, the
Company may increase its tax liability for the unrecognized tax benefits by up
to $1,500.&#160;&#160;In addition, the Company&#8217;s 2001 through</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> 2007 tax</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> years remain subject to examination by
major tax jurisdictions due to our net operating loss carryforwards.
</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Deferred tax assets include benefits
expected to be realized from the utilization of alternative minimum tax credit
carryforwards of $759, which do not expire, and net operating loss carryforwards
totaling $449,000, which begin expiring in 2022. Approximately $396,000 of the
net operating loss carryforwards are limited under Internal Revenue Code Section
382, and approximately $23,000 is not expected to be realized prior to
expiration, and therefore, a valuation allowance has been recorded of
$8,119.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">12. FAIR VALUE OF FINANCIAL
INSTRUMENTS</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The fair value of a financial instrument
is defined as the amount at which the instrument could be exchanged in an arm's
length transaction between knowledgeable, willing parties. The fair value of
long term debt is estimated based on discounting expected cash flows at the
rates currently offered to the Company for debt with similar remaining
maturities. As of December&#160;31, 2007 and 2006 respectively, the carrying
value of long-term debt was greater than its fair value by approximately
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">$136,800 and</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> $112,200.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">13. BENEFIT
PLAN&#8212;401(k)</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Republic has a defined contribution
retirement plan covering substantially all eligible employees. The Company
matches up to 6% of eligible employees' wages. Employees are generally vested in
matching contributions after three years of service with the Company. Employees
are also permitted to make pre-tax contributions of up to 90% (up to the annual
Internal Revenue Code limit) and after-tax contributions of up to 10% of their
annual compensation. The Company's expense under this plan was </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">$2,941</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, $2,266, and $1,660 for the years ended
December&#160;31, 2007, 2006 and 2005, respectively.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: #000000">14. IMPAIRMENT LOSS
AND ACCRUED AIRCRAFT RETURN COSTS</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Pursuant to the aircraft lease
agreements, the Company </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">was</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">required to return Saab 340 aircraft to
the lessor in specified conditions. Based upon flight schedules and maintenance
costs, return costs were estimated and accrued. Each year the Company decreased
the accrual for actual costs incurred and adjusted the accrual for its revised
estimate of expected return costs. In December 2005, Shuttle </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">America</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">&#8217;s turboprop code-share agreement with
United expired thus allowing for the return of our Saab aircraft to the lessor.
An agreement was reached with the lessors that released the Company of any
further financial obligations upon return of the aircraft resulting in a $4,218
reduction in the accrued liability. In 2006, we recorded a gain of $2,050
relating to the disposition of Saab aircraft and spare
parts.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The following table reflects impairment
costs and accrued aircraft return costs for the years ended</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> December 31, 2005 and
2006.</font></font></div>

              <td align="left" valign="bottom" width="40%">
                <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 9pt; TEXT-INDENT: -9pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">December 31,
      2006</font></font></div>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">(2) Write off of US Airways
receivable.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"><a name="item9">ITEM 9. CHANGES IN AND
DISAGREEMENTS WITH ACCOUNTANTS ON ACCOUNTING AND FINANCIAL
DISCLOSURE</a></font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">There were no disagreements with
accountants on accounting and financial disclosure.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"><a name="item9a">ITEM 9A. CONTROLS AND
PROCEDURES</a></font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Evaluation of Disclosure Controls and
Procedures.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">We maintain "disclosure controls and
procedures", as such term is defined under Securities Exchange Act
Rule&#160;13a-15(e), that are designed to ensure that information required to be
disclosed in our Exchange Act reports is recorded, processed, summarized and
reported within the time periods specified in the SEC's rules and forms, and
that such information is accumulated and communicated to our management,
including our Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer, as
appropriate, to allow timely decisions regarding required disclosures. In
designing and evaluating the disclosure controls and procedures, our management
recognized that any controls and procedures, no matter how well designed and
operated, can provide only reasonable assurance of achieving the desired control
objectives and our management necessarily was required to apply its judgment in
evaluating the cost-benefit relationship of possible controls and procedures. We
have carried out an evaluation, as of the end of the period covered by this
report, under the supervision and with the participation of our management,
including our Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer, of the
effectiveness of the design and operation of our disclosure controls and
procedures. Based upon their evaluation and subject to the foregoing, the Chief
Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer concluded that our disclosure
controls and procedures were effective in ensuring that material information
relating to us is made known to the Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial
Officer by others within&#160;the Company&#160;during the period in which this
report was being prepared.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Management&#8217;s Annual Report on Internal
Control Over Financial Reporting</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Management is responsible for
establishing and maintaining adequate internal control over financial reporting,
as such term is defined in Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f) under the Securities
Exchange Act of 1934. Our internal control over financial reporting is designed
to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting
and the preparation of financial statements for external purposed in accordance
with accounting principles generally accepted in the </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">United States of America</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Because of its inherent limitations,
internal control over financial reporting may not prevent or detect
misstatements. Projections of any evaluation of effectiveness to future periods
are subject to the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes
in conditions, or that the degree of compliance with the policies may
deteriorate.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Under the supervision and with the
participation of the Company&#8217;s Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial
Officer, the Company&#8217;s management conducted an evaluation of the effectiveness
of our internal control over financial reporting as of December 31,
200</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">7 </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">using the criteria issued by the
Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission in </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic">Internal
Control-Integrated Framework</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">. Based on that evaluation, the
Company&#8217;s management concluded that our internal control over financial
reporting was effective as of December 31, 200</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">7</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Management&#8217;s assessment of the
effectiveness of our internal control over financial reporting as of December
31, 200</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">7 </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">has been audited by Deloitte&#160;&amp;
Touche LLP, an independent registered public accounting firm, which also audited
our Consolidated Financial Statements. Deloitte &amp; Touche LLP&#8217;s report on
management&#8217;s assessment of internal control over financial reporting appears on
page </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff">50
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">herein.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"><a name="item9b">ITEM 9B. OTHER
INFORMATION</a></font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Not applicable.</font></font></div><br>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"><a name="part111">PART
III</a></font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><a name="item10"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">ITEM 10.
DIRECTORS</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">EXECUTIVE OFFICERS </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">AND CORPORATE
GOVERNANCE</font></a></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Directors</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">The information set forth under the
caption "Proposal No.&#160;1&#8212;Election of Directors" in the Company's definitive
Proxy Statement to be used in connection with the 2008 Annual</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000"> Meeting of Stockholders is incorporated
herein by reference.&#160;</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Executive Officers</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">See "Part&#160;I&#8212;Executive Officers of
the Company."</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Code of Ethics</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">We have adopted a Code of Ethics within
the meaning of Item 406(b) of SEC Regulation S-K. This Code of Ethics applies to
our principal executive officer, principal financial officer and principal
accounting officer. This Code of Ethics is publicly available on our website at
</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: italic">www.rjet.com</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">. If we make substantive amendments to
this Code of Ethics or grant any waiver, including any implicit waiver, we will
disclose the nature of such amendment or waiver on our website or in a report on
Form 8-K within four days of such amendment or waiver.</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Section
16(a) Beneficial Ownership Reporting Compliance</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Section 16(a) of the Securities Exchange
Act of 1934, as amended (the &#8220;Exchange Act&#8221;), requires that Company&#8217;s executive
officers and directors, and person who beneficially own more than ten percent of
the Company&#8217;s common stock, to file initial reports of ownership and reports of
changes in ownership with the SEC and the National Association of Securities
Dealers, Inc. Executive officers, directors, and greater than ten percent
beneficial owners are required by SEC regulations to furnish the Company with
copies of all Section 16(a) forms they file. Based upon a review of the copies
of such forms furnished to the Company and written representations from the
Company&#8217;s executive officers, directors and greater, we believe that during
fiscal&#160;&#160;2007 all</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">
Section 16(a) filing requirements applicable to its executive officers,
directors and greater than ten percent beneficial owners were complied with.
</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Corporate Governance</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

information set forth under the caption "Corporate Governance" in the Company's

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">We

consolidated financial statements of Republic Airways Holdings Inc. and
subsidiaries and the effectiveness of Republic Airways Holdings Inc.&#8217;s internal
control over financial reporting, (which report expresses an unqualified opinion
and includes explanatory paragraphs referring to Notes 1 and 2 to the
consolidated financial statements that (i) substantially all revenues are
derived from code-share agreements with US Airways, Inc., Delta Air Lines, Inc.,
AMR Corp., the parent of American Airlines, Inc., United Air Lines, Inc.,
Continental Airlines, Inc., Frontier Airlines, Inc., (ii) on January 1, 2006,
the Company adopted Statement of Financial Accounting Standards No. 123 (revised
2004), <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Share-Based
Payment</font>, using the modified prospective transition method and (iii) on
January 1, 2007, the Company adopted the provisions of FASB Interpretation No.
48, <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Accounting for Uncertainty
in Income Taxes &#8211; an Interpretation of FASB Statement No. 109</font>) appearing
in this Annual Report on Form 10-K of Republic Airways Holdings Inc. for the
year ended December 31, 2007.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">/s/ DELO</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">IT</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">TE &amp; TOUCHE LLP</font></font></div>
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Indianapolis</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">, </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">Indiana</font></font></div>
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">February 19,

    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">1. I have reviewed this report on Form

does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a
material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the
circumstances under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect
to the period covered by this report;</font></font></div>

    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">3. Based on my knowledge, the financial
statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly
present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations
and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this
report;</font></font></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">4. The registrant&#8217;s other certifying

controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(e) and
15d-15(e)) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Exchange
Act Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f))for the registrant and

procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed
under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the
registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by
others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this
report is being prepared;</font></font></div>

    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">b) Designed such internal control over
financial reporting, or caused such internal control over financial reporting to
be designed under our supervision, to provide reasonable assurance regarding the
reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements
for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting
principles;</font></font></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt"><br></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">c) Evaluated the effectiveness of the
registrant&#8217;s disclosure controls and procedures and presented in this report our
conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure controls and procedures,
as of the end of the period covered by this report based on such evaluation;
and</font></font></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">d) Disclosed in this report any change
in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting that occurred
during the registrant&#8217;s most recent fiscal quarter (the registrant&#8217;s fourth

is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant&#8217;s internal control

    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">5. The registrant&#8217;s other certifying
officer and I have disclosed, based on our most recent evaluation of internal
control over financial reporting, to the registrant&#8217;s auditors and the audit
committee of the registrant&#8217;s the board of directors (or persons performing the
equivalent functions):</font></font></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">a) All significant deficiencies and
material weaknesses in the design or operation of internal control over
financial reporting which are reasonably likely to adversely affect the
registrant&#8217;s ability to record, process, summarize and report financial
information; and</font></font></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt; TEXT-INDENT: 27pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; COLOR: #000000">b) Any fraud, whether or not material,
that involves management or other employees who have a significant role in the
registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting.</font></font></div>
    <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
      <div>

information contained in the Report fairly presents, in all material respects,
the financial condition and results of operations of the Company at the end of,
